About
STARDOM awaits you! Step into the spotlight as you accept your exclusive invitation to Madame Tussauds London, the home of famous fun in the capital. Join your favourite celebs at the ULTIMATE A-list party, strut your stuff on the catwalk with Cara, take the hot seat alongside will.i.am in The Voice Experience or join the Royal Family on the iconic balcony. Test your bravery in Alien: Escape then explore the jungles of Kong: Skull Island. Hail a London cab and journey through 400 years of the capital’s history before joining the Marvel Super Heroes for a crime-fighting adventure. Then use the force to be transported to a galaxy far, far away and star in the action with the greats of the Star Wars universe. So what are you waiting for? COME ON IN!
Duration: 2-3 hours

    Fun for all ages! Recommend a visit
    We were a group of five, three adults and two teenagers, ages between 15-67 years and everyone had an amazing time! I have an autistic 16 year old and he had a sensory overloads midway through, so we asked an employee if they had a quiet room he could rest in for a few minutes, and the response was exemplary! They had a quiet room he was able to rest in, they brought him water and the service was just so great. I’m so grateful for their help and how they handled the situation. After ten minutes we were able to continue our journey through the museum and everyone was happy, the staff told us if there was anything we needed we should just let them know. This was a really positive experience. The museum is huge and the Marvel and Star Wars section was our favorites. Absolutely worth a visit!

    Hyped expectations and exorbitant entrance fee but great disappointment.
    This place is supposed to be a must visit for any visitor to London, but was a great disappointment. The entrance is 45 GBP per person which itself is a waste of money. The displays are few and they have removed a number of historically important and famous persons. They have few Hollywood and Bollywood celebrities but nothing else. Only consolation was there was no waiting in the que to enter and there were very few visitors. I am sure the visitor number will go down further unless they improve exhibition and make the entrance fee reasonable especially in this hard times.
    MadameTussaudsLondon

MadameTussaudsLondon
Hello, Thank you for taking the time and trouble to leave this review of our attraction. I am sorry to read that your visit was not quite what you had expected. We are a premier London attraction, and we always want to ensure all our guests have a great time with us, so I apologize if your visit fell short in any way. I am sorry there were more stairs than expected. Madame Tussauds London is housed in a very old heritage building, and unfortunately is nature and layout does mean that there are a lot of stairs around the attraction. We would always recommend our guests speak to our team members if they require to use one of our lifts, as they are all more than happy to assist with this. I am also sorry that some of our figures fell short of your expectations. We have a dedicated team of artists that check all our figures before and after closing, and who conduct regular walkarounds throughout the day, to ensure that the quality of our figures always remains high, so I can only apologize if some of the figures were not what you had expected. While it's great to read that you loved our Chamber of Horrors, I apologize that our Marvel film and Spirit of London ride fell below your expectations. We appreciate that these areas are not reflective of what you would like to see at our attraction. Thank you again for taking the time to share this feedback, we will pass this on to our team so that we can continue to improve. Kind Regards, Stella Guest Experience Team Madame Tussauds London

Not as polished as was expected.......
Nov 2024 • Couples
The venue was okay, but to be honest I'm finding it hard to say much positive to be honest. Arrived early to be told and I quote "you'll have to go away and come back at 6pm". Came back at 6pm to go in and start the tour. Weirdly a lot of Bollywood actors models scattered all over the place with no apparent theme. Some of the models were spot on, however others appeared a little tired and rehashed from the past. Taylor Swift and Dua Lipa were bang on, but the Beatles and the Bond collection were quite obviously old models which need refreshing. The best model likeness wise is the Lewis Hamiltion closely followed by Taylor Swift.

The worst........David Beckham and oh my God...Sean Connery, that was unbelievably bad, with no real likeness to him at all. George Harrison looked like a heroine addict on a day pass. The Star Wars exhibit........missed opportunity big time.Hardly any characters from the final 3 episodes in the franchise, no driids....no Emperor, no Dooku....nothing.

I won't be going back there , it was very tired in its presentation. Not as polished as you would expect from a "world famous" exhibition.
